The total amount of liquid product was measured using NMR (AV 500) spectroscopy, in which 0.5 mL electrolyte was mixed with 0.1 ml D2O (deuterated water), and 0.05 μL dimethyl sulfoxide (DMSO, Sigma, 99.99%) was added as an internal standard. Assuming that two electrons are needed to produce one formate molecule, the FE can be calculated as follows: FEHCOO− = 2 F × nHCOO−/(itotal × t), where F is the Faraday constant and t is the time, thenjHCOO−=FEHCOO−×itotal×electrodearea−1.\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
